WEBVTT

00:00:29.217 --> 00:00:30.302
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:00:33.388 --> 00:00:35.014
CHARACTERS, EVENTS, ORGANIZATIONS,
AND PLACES IN THIS DRAMA ARE FICTITIOUS

00:00:35.015 --> 00:00:36.308
ALL CHILD ACTORS AND ANIMALS
FILMED IN A SAFE ENVIRONMENT

00:00:49.071 --> 00:00:50.072
What is it?

00:00:52.115 --> 00:00:53.158
Are you okay?

00:00:57.871 --> 00:01:00.414
Yes, it was just the lights.

00:01:00.415 --> 00:01:01.666
I'm fine.

00:01:02.793 --> 00:01:05.379
No, you don't look fine.

00:01:06.797 --> 00:01:07.880
I am.

00:01:07.881 --> 00:01:12.594
I won't cause you any trouble,
especially during the three-month trial.

00:01:18.058 --> 00:01:19.684
It was my first time
hearing that sound.

00:01:21.353 --> 00:01:25.856
It kind of sounded like tiny bits
of metal clinking or ice rattling.

00:01:25.857 --> 00:01:27.108
Right, the door!

00:01:27.109 --> 00:01:29.611
I think it came from outside the lab.

00:01:30.779 --> 00:01:31.862
EPISODE 4

00:01:31.863 --> 00:01:33.155
But I'm not sure what that sound was

00:01:33.156 --> 00:01:35.491
or why I was suddenly reminded
of the explosion.

00:01:37.035 --> 00:01:38.869
From everything I've heard so far,

00:01:38.870 --> 00:01:41.998
it's most likely
that it's a second trigger.

00:01:42.666 --> 00:01:44.334
A second trigger?

00:01:45.669 --> 00:01:46.794
It's nice to meet you.

00:01:46.795 --> 00:01:48.546
I'm Song Haran, the lead designer.

00:01:48.547 --> 00:01:52.383
It seems that
seeing her again acted as a trigger.

00:01:52.384 --> 00:01:55.428
She seems to have stimulated something,

00:01:55.429 --> 00:01:57.680
allowing you to remember
another piece of your past.

00:01:57.681 --> 00:02:00.349
Wait. No…

00:02:00.350 --> 00:02:03.060
That doesn't make any sense.

00:02:03.061 --> 00:02:05.187
I recalled everything seven years ago.

00:02:05.188 --> 00:02:09.191
When I first saw her at Jamsugyo,
I remembered everything in Boston.

00:02:09.192 --> 00:02:11.527
How are you sure it was everything?

00:02:11.528 --> 00:02:14.947
Well, because it was only
a temporary side effect

00:02:14.948 --> 00:02:18.075
from the shock of the accident.

00:02:18.076 --> 00:02:22.413
You're saying you remembered
everything at that moment?

00:02:22.414 --> 00:02:26.959
Yes. And I've never recalled
any new sounds or images since then.

00:02:26.960 --> 00:02:28.294
Not once.

00:02:28.295 --> 00:02:29.588
What if…

00:02:30.964 --> 00:02:32.966
Like this…

00:02:34.718 --> 00:02:38.805
What if there is still an empty spot
in your memories that you're not aware of?

00:02:39.723 --> 00:02:41.975
An empty spot?

00:02:42.559 --> 00:02:45.437
You seem like
a completely different person now.

00:02:46.021 --> 00:02:49.941
I can even picture
how hard you tried to change yourself.

00:02:51.359 --> 00:02:56.947
The harder you try to shake off the past,
the more your defense mechanisms kick in.

00:02:56.948 --> 00:02:59.700
Your unconscious mind
may overwrite painful memories

00:02:59.701 --> 00:03:02.913
to keep you from suffering any longer.

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:09.586
It means there's still
an empty spot inside you.

00:03:12.088 --> 00:03:16.342
If that sound
is a part of that empty spot,

00:03:16.343 --> 00:03:18.553
is it a signal from the past

00:03:20.222 --> 00:03:23.600
telling me it's linked
to the explosion seven years ago?

00:03:26.937 --> 00:03:29.648
We can't be sure
of anything right now, but…

00:03:30.315 --> 00:03:31.982
it's certain that

00:03:31.983 --> 00:03:35.236
she's the one who has the key
to that empty spot inside you.

00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:39.282
You don't seem happy to see me.

00:03:39.950 --> 00:03:43.203
I mustered up my courage
to come and celebrate starting the trial.

00:03:47.457 --> 00:03:48.667
That's cold!

00:03:49.209 --> 00:03:53.672
Mmm. I always give a water show
to people I'm excited to see.

00:03:56.675 --> 00:03:58.343
Hey, look who it is!

00:03:58.927 --> 00:04:00.302
How have you been, Genius?

00:04:01.555 --> 00:04:05.099
- How are you?
- It's been such a long time.

00:04:05.100 --> 00:04:06.684
What are you doing here so early?

00:04:06.685 --> 00:04:08.686
I wanted to have your coffee.

00:04:08.687 --> 00:04:10.646
I'm aching
from not having any for so long.

00:04:10.647 --> 00:04:12.815
Really? Then I should make you some now.

00:04:12.816 --> 00:04:13.941
Come on in.

00:04:13.942 --> 00:04:15.986
- Let's go, Genius.
- Come inside.

00:04:18.321 --> 00:04:21.490
If you don't want to suffer again
because of your past,

00:04:21.491 --> 00:04:23.993
it would be best
to keep a distance from her.

00:04:23.994 --> 00:04:26.120
To protect yourself,

00:04:26.121 --> 00:04:29.332
a lock is safer than a key at the moment.

00:04:30.083 --> 00:04:31.960
A lock…

00:04:39.801 --> 00:04:42.094
- Sit down, roomie.
- Okay.

00:04:42.095 --> 00:04:44.930
Here's some coffee for my VVIP.

00:04:44.931 --> 00:04:46.641
Thank you.

00:04:47.017 --> 00:04:48.100
Huh?

00:04:48.101 --> 00:04:51.479
Right. It must have recovered
from the transplant shock.

00:04:52.272 --> 00:04:55.566
Good thing I repotted it, right?

00:04:56.818 --> 00:04:58.904
- Yes.
- Right.

00:04:59.738 --> 00:05:01.323
It's a good thing you took it out.

00:05:04.200 --> 00:05:07.077
Even if I break down again,
I'll stay by her side.

00:05:07.078 --> 00:05:08.162
Mmm.

00:05:08.163 --> 00:05:11.457
She's the one
who gave me the life I have now.

00:05:11.458 --> 00:05:15.128
I would have died
if it hadn't been for her.

00:05:17.672 --> 00:05:18.798
Why are you staring at me?

00:05:19.633 --> 00:05:21.635
Mmm… Can't I look at you?

00:05:22.427 --> 00:05:24.512
Here. Cheers.

00:05:34.022 --> 00:05:35.774
Whatever's hiding in that empty spot,

00:05:36.733 --> 00:05:38.151
I'm going to deal with it.

00:05:38.902 --> 00:05:42.697
As long as she becomes happy,
I don't care what happens.

00:05:43.907 --> 00:05:45.283
I'll be careful

00:05:45.992 --> 00:05:49.287
so my existence doesn't reopen
her old wounds…

00:05:50.956 --> 00:05:53.458
and I'll do everything I can for her
before I leave again.

00:06:01.049 --> 00:06:02.968
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

00:06:05.261 --> 00:06:06.595
Did you check the data?

00:06:06.596 --> 00:06:07.846
Yes.

00:06:07.847 --> 00:06:10.891
The background team's research
was a little lacking.

00:06:10.892 --> 00:06:12.476
When did you organize all this?

00:06:12.477 --> 00:06:16.814
There was a lot of modernized material,
so I researched traditional hanok.

00:06:16.815 --> 00:06:20.859
I guess a Korean
should have researched traditional hanok.

00:06:21.945 --> 00:06:24.571
Okay,
I'll send this over to the EA team,

00:06:24.572 --> 00:06:27.866
and we can go down to Gyeongju on Tuesday.

00:06:27.867 --> 00:06:29.702
Oh. I'll join you a day late.

00:06:29.703 --> 00:06:33.205
Ms. Kim said she'll send over
the dancheong design draft on Tuesday.

00:06:33.206 --> 00:06:34.207
Mmm. Okay.

00:06:35.166 --> 00:06:37.501
But how will you get there, then?

00:06:37.502 --> 00:06:40.838
- I'll rent a car.
- Are you sure?

00:06:40.839 --> 00:06:43.883
I'll be absolutely fine.

00:06:48.680 --> 00:06:50.431
Hey, stop writing that.

00:06:50.432 --> 00:06:51.766
Fine.

00:06:52.350 --> 00:06:54.476
- Geez!
- We'd like to pay.

00:06:54.477 --> 00:06:55.478
BEN IS AN IDIOT

00:06:56.646 --> 00:06:58.397
Ms. Song!

00:07:00.817 --> 00:07:02.235
What is he doing?

00:07:03.778 --> 00:07:04.863
You're done with work, right?

00:07:05.864 --> 00:07:07.198
Are you busy, by any chance?

00:07:07.657 --> 00:07:08.700
Nice!

00:07:10.076 --> 00:07:12.286
Then get in.

00:07:12.287 --> 00:07:16.248
- What? Where are we going?
- There's a car coming.

00:07:16.249 --> 00:07:21.336
I have a special lecture tomorrow,
so wrap up the contract with our buyer.

00:07:21.337 --> 00:07:22.964
- Yes, ma'am.
- Get in. Come on.

00:07:24.007 --> 00:07:25.924
Watch your head.

00:07:25.925 --> 00:07:26.926
Sorry!

00:07:28.261 --> 00:07:29.304
Oh, yeah.

00:07:30.430 --> 00:07:33.974
Did you just say, "Oh, yeah"?

00:07:33.975 --> 00:07:34.976
Those two.

00:07:35.852 --> 00:07:36.936
Keep an eye on them.

00:07:37.395 --> 00:07:38.396
Bye, then.

00:07:42.317 --> 00:07:44.068
So they weren't lying to me.

00:07:47.655 --> 00:07:49.823
We came all the way here for chicken?

00:07:49.824 --> 00:07:52.117
This is a must in Korea.

00:07:52.118 --> 00:07:54.496
Hangang River, picnic mat, and chicken.

00:07:55.246 --> 00:07:57.749
I'm also a tourist from abroad, you know.

00:07:58.500 --> 00:08:01.251
Wow!

00:08:01.252 --> 00:08:03.420
The Hangang River is so nice.

00:08:12.347 --> 00:08:14.224
I have something to give you. Sit down.

00:08:17.185 --> 00:08:19.895
There are 0.3, 0.4, 5, 6,

00:08:19.896 --> 00:08:22.648
oil-based, water-based,
nib tip, and ballpoint pens.

00:08:22.649 --> 00:08:25.359
Wait. Are you opening a stationery store?

00:08:25.360 --> 00:08:27.694
Who has this many pens?

00:08:27.695 --> 00:08:30.865
I have a habit of buying new pens
for people who lose their pens.

00:08:34.327 --> 00:08:36.955
There should at least be
one pen that you like.

00:08:42.710 --> 00:08:45.672
But the trial hasn't started yet.

00:08:46.339 --> 00:08:48.674
This is like a preview.

00:08:48.675 --> 00:08:49.925
A preview of what?

00:08:49.926 --> 00:08:53.345
I'll be away for about two weeks
starting Wednesday

00:08:53.346 --> 00:08:54.389
for a field survey.

00:08:55.223 --> 00:08:56.766
I said we'd get close,

00:08:57.433 --> 00:09:00.060
but if I left without doing anything,
nothing would change.

00:09:00.061 --> 00:09:01.187
And I didn't want that.

00:09:02.605 --> 00:09:04.356
So…

00:09:05.441 --> 00:09:06.568
will you take this, too?

00:09:08.611 --> 00:09:09.612
Oh…

00:09:10.363 --> 00:09:12.197
SEOUL DESTINATIONS LIST

00:09:12.198 --> 00:09:14.032
Why are you giving this to me?

00:09:14.033 --> 00:09:17.161
Choose where to go first
so we can go together later.

00:09:19.497 --> 00:09:21.791
The chicken's here.
I'll go get it.

00:09:22.625 --> 00:09:24.252
Can you clean that up?

00:09:25.378 --> 00:09:28.631
Oh. It's this way.
We have to eat chicken here, so hurry!

00:09:35.763 --> 00:09:36.973
"That person"?

00:09:39.934 --> 00:09:41.977
The night view is beautiful.

00:09:41.978 --> 00:09:43.061
Right?

00:09:43.062 --> 00:09:46.148
How about going to Jamsugyo on Christmas?
It's the best spot

00:09:46.149 --> 00:09:48.066
to watch the fireworks.

00:09:48.067 --> 00:09:49.861
- I'd love that.
- Jamsugyo?

00:09:51.154 --> 00:09:52.238
Cheers.

00:10:02.081 --> 00:10:03.540
Goodness.

00:10:03.541 --> 00:10:05.042
We're really stuck.

00:10:05.043 --> 00:10:07.753
I heard they're showing fireworks
at 7:00.

00:10:07.754 --> 00:10:09.339
We're not moving at all.

00:10:12.300 --> 00:10:15.385
How long will it take?
I have an important meeting.

00:10:15.386 --> 00:10:18.556
If it's urgent, it would be faster
to just walk across the bridge.

00:10:21.935 --> 00:10:23.185
Mr. Yoon.

00:10:23.186 --> 00:10:25.104
The traffic's bad
since it's Christmas Eve.

00:10:26.397 --> 00:10:27.981
Really?

00:10:27.982 --> 00:10:29.942
Then take your time.

00:10:29.943 --> 00:10:31.236
All right.

00:11:12.443 --> 00:11:15.570
Hey, Kang Hyeokchan.
Why aren't you picking up?

00:11:15.571 --> 00:11:17.991
Sorry, I fell asleep.

00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:20.284
Maybe I have insomnia.

00:11:20.285 --> 00:11:23.870
My sleep pattern is messed up,
so I'm sleeping at random times.

00:11:23.871 --> 00:11:26.748
They said it helps with insomnia.

00:11:26.749 --> 00:11:28.960
Try listening to it
when you can't sleep. Okay?

00:11:36.009 --> 00:11:37.467
Let's go.

00:11:37.468 --> 00:11:39.177
- What? Right now?
- Yes.

00:11:39.178 --> 00:11:40.679
Should we order fried chicken?

00:11:40.680 --> 00:11:42.597
- Isn't seasoned chicken better?
- Hang on.

00:11:42.598 --> 00:11:44.099
No, fried is better.

00:11:44.100 --> 00:11:46.310
- Here you go!
- What's this?

00:11:46.311 --> 00:11:47.811
You won some free chicken.

00:11:47.812 --> 00:11:49.980
- We can have this? Wow.
- Of course.

00:11:49.981 --> 00:11:51.690
It's still warm, so enjoy.

00:11:51.691 --> 00:11:53.525
Thank you.

00:11:54.819 --> 00:11:57.779
Come on. These are valuable,
so don't forget them.

00:11:59.782 --> 00:12:01.909
Chicken was too predictable, right?

00:12:02.577 --> 00:12:05.120
Let's go with charcoal-grilled meat.

00:12:05.121 --> 00:12:06.788
Ben recommended--

00:12:06.789 --> 00:12:09.083
All right, fine.

00:12:09.876 --> 00:12:11.001
But what's with these?

00:12:11.002 --> 00:12:12.503
Ah.

00:12:13.129 --> 00:12:16.549
We're going to cross Jamsugyo with these.
It's the fastest way.

00:12:17.633 --> 00:12:21.846
I'm sorry, but I'd like to just go now.

00:12:25.058 --> 00:12:26.641
No way.

00:12:26.642 --> 00:12:28.435
Can you not ride a bike?

00:12:28.436 --> 00:12:30.103
No, it's not that…

00:12:30.104 --> 00:12:32.105
No, it's okay.

00:12:32.106 --> 00:12:34.400
It's nothing to be ashamed of.

00:12:34.942 --> 00:12:37.027
- I'll return them.
- No, I…

00:12:37.028 --> 00:12:39.280
I know how to ride a bike, but…

00:12:41.866 --> 00:12:44.076
Fine. Let's go, then.

00:12:44.077 --> 00:12:45.078
Okay!

00:12:45.787 --> 00:12:46.871
All right.

00:12:47.497 --> 00:12:49.998
Since it's boring to just ride there,
how about a bet?

00:12:49.999 --> 00:12:52.626
The last one there buys dinner. Okay?

00:12:52.627 --> 00:12:54.252
No, there's no need…

00:12:54.253 --> 00:12:55.338
- Let's just--
- Ready, go!

00:12:57.215 --> 00:12:59.466
That's cheating.

00:13:05.515 --> 00:13:06.516
Oh…

00:13:07.308 --> 00:13:09.184
Whoa. Wait…

00:13:09.185 --> 00:13:11.353
Hang on! My leg…

00:13:11.354 --> 00:13:12.896
Wait, wait!

00:13:12.897 --> 00:13:14.690
What is it? What's wrong with your leg?

00:13:16.943 --> 00:13:17.944
It's long.

00:13:18.486 --> 00:13:19.569
What?

00:13:19.570 --> 00:13:21.071
Ah…

00:13:21.072 --> 00:13:22.907
Geez.

00:13:33.793 --> 00:13:34.794
Wow!

00:13:36.170 --> 00:13:37.171
Wow.

00:13:40.758 --> 00:13:41.759
Whoa.

00:14:12.540 --> 00:14:15.877
Wow, it's beautiful.

00:14:16.419 --> 00:14:17.420
Isn't it?

00:14:25.803 --> 00:14:28.264
Wow. The Hangang River is nice.

00:14:28.848 --> 00:14:31.224
Were you mimicking me?

00:14:31.225 --> 00:14:33.935
But that's not how you do it.

00:14:33.936 --> 00:14:37.314
Wow!

00:14:37.315 --> 00:14:39.566
Hangang River is really nice.

00:14:39.567 --> 00:14:40.650
What's the difference?

00:14:40.651 --> 00:14:42.110
- It sounds the same.
- It's different.

00:14:43.279 --> 00:14:44.864
I won, so you're buying.

00:14:47.200 --> 00:14:48.701
We haven't even gotten there yet.

00:14:55.458 --> 00:14:57.710
Good morning.

00:14:59.253 --> 00:15:00.795
Ah!

00:15:00.796 --> 00:15:02.882
- Hi, Hadam.
- Good morning.

00:15:04.342 --> 00:15:06.218
You know
Yougyum's coming today, right?

00:15:06.219 --> 00:15:08.094
He's coming at 7:00 p.m.,
so don't be late.

00:15:08.095 --> 00:15:11.097
Of course. We've been waiting
impatiently for this day.

00:15:11.098 --> 00:15:14.142
We'll have you rascals
sit down in front of us

00:15:14.143 --> 00:15:16.770
while we look him over from head to toe…

00:15:16.771 --> 00:15:19.648
Hey! I'm not done talking.

00:15:19.649 --> 00:15:21.150
You did go on for quite a bit.

00:15:23.319 --> 00:15:27.072
Haran, she can't be serious
about getting married, can she?

00:15:27.073 --> 00:15:30.243
I don't know. We'll see.

00:15:33.537 --> 00:15:36.748
CHEONGSOL BASEBALL TEAM CHA YOUGYUM
IS JOINING THE MAJOR LEAGUE

00:15:40.920 --> 00:15:42.295
No way. It's Han Sora.

00:15:42.296 --> 00:15:43.381
She came to school today?

00:15:44.215 --> 00:15:46.633
What? Who are you?

00:15:46.634 --> 00:15:48.051
Why do you want my number?

00:15:49.136 --> 00:15:52.889
Because I'm interested in you, of course.

00:15:54.475 --> 00:15:56.476
I'm not interested in you at all.

00:15:56.477 --> 00:15:57.936
And I have a girlfriend.

00:15:57.937 --> 00:15:59.354
Yougyum.

00:15:59.355 --> 00:16:00.439
Hey, Hadam.

00:16:04.068 --> 00:16:05.151
What's going on?

00:16:05.152 --> 00:16:06.528
It's nothing.

00:16:06.529 --> 00:16:09.323
Ah. Is she your girlfriend?

00:16:10.825 --> 00:16:12.243
I'll see you later.

00:16:18.040 --> 00:16:19.959
Who is she? Do you know her?

00:16:20.584 --> 00:16:23.837
Not at all.
It's the last time I'll even speak to her.

00:16:23.838 --> 00:16:25.547
Hey, don't you know? It's her.

00:16:25.548 --> 00:16:27.757
- Han Sora, the girl group trainee--
- Hadam!

00:16:27.758 --> 00:16:30.135
Have a good day. I'll see you later.

00:16:31.971 --> 00:16:34.097
- She must really like you.
- Be quiet, will you?

00:16:34.098 --> 00:16:35.473
Come on!

00:16:35.474 --> 00:16:37.392
- She's so pretty, though.
- Right?

00:16:37.393 --> 00:16:38.601
Shut up, you guys.

00:16:38.602 --> 00:16:39.979
She has her eyes set on you.
You should date her.

00:16:40.521 --> 00:16:42.105
Be quiet. Shut up.

00:16:42.106 --> 00:16:44.108
That's the problem
with handsome guys.

00:16:44.984 --> 00:16:46.110
"Han Sora"?

00:17:04.837 --> 00:17:06.130
Hmm?

00:17:19.852 --> 00:17:21.853
This is Design Team 1 of Nana Atelier--

00:17:21.854 --> 00:17:23.439
Why isn't anyone picking up?

00:17:26.067 --> 00:17:27.317
Why are you calling here?

00:17:27.318 --> 00:17:29.028
This is urgent. Listen carefully.

00:17:29.153 --> 00:17:31.989
It's a womenswear lecture,
but I brought menswear materials.

00:17:32.114 --> 00:17:35.492
- That's on me. We don't have much time.
- Taxi! Taxi! Over here!

00:17:35.493 --> 00:17:37.702
I need you here in 30 minutes.

00:17:37.703 --> 00:17:40.206
What do I do?

00:17:44.877 --> 00:17:47.545
- Hey, my neighbor!
- Oh… Do you have some time?

00:17:47.546 --> 00:17:49.506
Sure, I'm totally free.

00:17:49.507 --> 00:17:51.216
I rented this car, so I'm taking a drive--

00:17:51.217 --> 00:17:53.134
That's great! Then…

00:17:53.135 --> 00:17:55.136
Then can you…

00:17:55.137 --> 00:17:57.555
I have an urgent meeting,
but I can't get a cab.

00:17:57.556 --> 00:17:59.724
It's a 15-minute drive.
Please give me a ride.

00:17:59.725 --> 00:18:01.851
Well, I…

00:18:01.852 --> 00:18:03.645
But I…

00:18:03.646 --> 00:18:04.814
Yeah?

00:18:05.815 --> 00:18:07.650
All right.

00:18:17.910 --> 00:18:20.662
Do you know you're driving
20 km an hour right now?

00:18:20.663 --> 00:18:22.664
You can drive up to 60 here.

00:18:22.665 --> 00:18:26.377
I'm sorry, but can't you go a bit faster?
I only have 20 minutes left.

00:18:28.003 --> 00:18:29.505
Okay.

00:18:35.010 --> 00:18:36.929
Watch out!

00:18:46.230 --> 00:18:47.606
Hey!

00:18:47.732 --> 00:18:49.525
Hey, get out.

00:18:50.860 --> 00:18:52.902
Get out of the car.

00:18:57.616 --> 00:18:59.993
I almost got hit because of you.

00:18:59.994 --> 00:19:02.204
You can't just cut in like that.

00:19:02.747 --> 00:19:06.375
I'm sorry. I'll take care of any damages.

00:19:06.959 --> 00:19:07.960
Uh…

00:19:09.128 --> 00:19:11.504
Okay. I'll pick it up right away.

00:19:11.505 --> 00:19:12.882
I'm so sorry.

00:19:28.731 --> 00:19:31.066
Ms. Song, look at me.

00:19:32.735 --> 00:19:34.235
I'm sorry about that.

00:19:34.236 --> 00:19:35.570
But everything's fine.

00:19:35.571 --> 00:19:38.198
I took care of everything. It's fine.

00:19:38.199 --> 00:19:40.658
Are you okay?
Are you sure you're not hurt?

00:19:40.659 --> 00:19:44.288
I shouldn't have
asked you for a ride.

00:19:45.164 --> 00:19:47.708
Nothing happened,
and no one's hurt. It's fine.

00:19:51.545 --> 00:19:52.963
MS. KIM

00:19:53.714 --> 00:19:56.592
I'm sorry, but I don't think
I can take you. Uh…

00:19:57.635 --> 00:20:01.095
There's a cab over there.
You're in a hurry, so go.

00:20:01.096 --> 00:20:04.307
I'll take care of everything here,
so don't worry.

00:20:07.394 --> 00:20:10.105
Getting close to someone
is really difficult…

00:20:10.689 --> 00:20:13.025
No, it's scary for me.

00:20:14.109 --> 00:20:16.237
If no one is special to me,

00:20:17.279 --> 00:20:19.573
then at least nothing bad will happen.

00:20:39.009 --> 00:20:40.094
Earlier…

00:20:45.015 --> 00:20:48.434
I'm sorry about what happened earlier.

00:20:48.435 --> 00:20:52.189
No, I'm sorry.
I shouldn't have forced you like that.

00:20:54.275 --> 00:20:55.860
It was because of your ear, right?

00:20:57.278 --> 00:20:59.279
It seemed that way.

00:21:05.828 --> 00:21:09.706
A few years ago,
Ben got injured because of me.

00:21:09.707 --> 00:21:11.834
There was a honk on my left side,

00:21:13.043 --> 00:21:14.628
but I couldn't react properly,

00:21:15.504 --> 00:21:16.589
like earlier.

00:21:18.632 --> 00:21:23.220
Since then, I told myself
I would never give anyone a ride,

00:21:24.305 --> 00:21:25.722
but…

00:21:25.723 --> 00:21:29.518
Today was the first time,
so I guess I was anxious.

00:21:30.936 --> 00:21:32.228
I'm sorry.

00:21:32.229 --> 00:21:33.647
You're scared

00:21:34.732 --> 00:21:35.983
of bad things happening,

00:21:36.650 --> 00:21:38.068
but I made you go through that.

00:21:42.531 --> 00:21:45.826
Your free trial
is proving to be effective, though.

00:21:47.786 --> 00:21:51.540
Back at the Hangang River,
and in the car earlier,

00:21:52.124 --> 00:21:53.583
it helped me a lot.

00:21:58.255 --> 00:22:01.926
I don't exactly have good memories
about Jamsugyo.

00:22:05.137 --> 00:22:08.306
I thought I'd only have sad memories
about it forever,

00:22:08.307 --> 00:22:09.767
but I realized I could smile there.

00:22:10.392 --> 00:22:15.356
Perhaps I can overwrite
those sad memories, too.

00:22:16.607 --> 00:22:18.192
I thought that for the first time.

00:22:19.276 --> 00:22:23.781
And I was really scared back in the car,
but I recovered quickly thanks to you.

00:22:25.491 --> 00:22:28.911
If it were a few days ago,
I would have just tried to flee again.

00:22:30.287 --> 00:22:31.413
But I won't now.

00:22:33.248 --> 00:22:35.750
At least until the trial is over,

00:22:35.751 --> 00:22:37.378
I won't enter my cave again.

00:22:38.921 --> 00:22:42.424
So don't blame yourself, okay?

00:22:48.681 --> 00:22:51.058
I'm relieved.

00:22:53.018 --> 00:22:54.103
To be honest,

00:22:55.437 --> 00:22:57.189
I was pretty scared.

00:22:58.983 --> 00:23:00.693
You just mustered up your courage,

00:23:02.027 --> 00:23:04.071
and I was worried you'd run away again.

00:23:05.280 --> 00:23:07.157
I said we'd have fun,

00:23:07.825 --> 00:23:11.412
but I thought I'd already ruined it.

00:23:13.706 --> 00:23:15.248
Keep teaching me.

00:23:15.249 --> 00:23:17.292
I'll do my best to learn.

00:23:23.799 --> 00:23:25.133
I'll get going now. Bye.

00:23:25.134 --> 00:23:26.676
Okay. Bye.

00:23:28.804 --> 00:23:29.971
Ah.

00:23:29.972 --> 00:23:31.348
I actually don't like…

00:23:32.725 --> 00:23:35.019
everything being okay and only having fun.

00:23:35.602 --> 00:23:37.354
That's fake friendship.

00:23:38.689 --> 00:23:41.024
Being able to tell each other
when you're not okay

00:23:41.025 --> 00:23:42.234
is real friendship, right?

00:23:44.945 --> 00:23:47.864
So let's tell each other in advance
if something's wrong

00:23:47.865 --> 00:23:49.950
so we won't have to feel guilty
like today.

00:23:50.909 --> 00:23:53.453
All right.

00:23:53.454 --> 00:23:56.205
But you should stop that
if you want real friendship.

00:23:56.206 --> 00:23:57.458
Stop what?

00:23:59.501 --> 00:24:02.463
You don't have to worry so much
about my hearing.

00:24:03.005 --> 00:24:04.297
What? Me?

00:24:05.549 --> 00:24:09.344
- I wasn't worried about that at all.
- It's pretty obvious, you know.

00:24:09.928 --> 00:24:13.891
Ever since you found out,
you've been standing to my right.

00:24:14.767 --> 00:24:19.228
I'm usually fine,
so you don't have to do that, okay?

00:24:19.229 --> 00:24:24.193
Well, it's been a long time
since I made a new friend,

00:24:24.860 --> 00:24:28.821
so I'm not really sure what I have to do.

00:24:28.822 --> 00:24:30.074
You seem mature,

00:24:31.200 --> 00:24:32.533
but you're a picky eater.

00:24:32.534 --> 00:24:34.912
You love Mr. Park's coffee,

00:24:35.496 --> 00:24:37.790
you ride a bike very well,

00:24:38.707 --> 00:24:41.418
and you pretend not to be,
but you're pretty caring.

00:24:42.419 --> 00:24:43.503
What?

00:24:43.504 --> 00:24:45.130
This is how you become friends.

00:24:46.423 --> 00:24:48.424
Slowly, without forcing anything,

00:24:48.425 --> 00:24:50.886
by finding out small things
about each other.

00:24:53.138 --> 00:24:56.140
I also don't like oysters.
They're like snot.

00:24:56.141 --> 00:24:58.142
What? Snot?

00:24:58.143 --> 00:24:59.812
I just told you more about myself.

00:25:01.730 --> 00:25:04.108
Is this not how you do it?

00:25:05.609 --> 00:25:06.984
It is. That's right.

00:25:06.985 --> 00:25:08.862
Give me your hand. I'll give you a stamp.

00:25:10.197 --> 00:25:12.032
Here. A "great job" stamp.

00:25:15.244 --> 00:25:18.163
I told you a secret,
so next time it's your turn.

00:25:21.083 --> 00:25:24.878
It doesn't have to be anything big.
Just a small one.

00:25:26.421 --> 00:25:27.422
Bye, then.

00:25:30.008 --> 00:25:31.093
Bye.

00:25:36.932 --> 00:25:37.933
A secret…

00:25:46.275 --> 00:25:48.317
Hmm. Hair, check.

00:25:48.318 --> 00:25:51.445
Your outfit's nice…
and your face is even nicer.

00:25:51.446 --> 00:25:54.115
You're perfect.

00:25:54.116 --> 00:25:55.741
I'm so nervous.

00:25:55.742 --> 00:25:58.327
I wasn't even this nervous
at the Comets press conference.

00:25:58.328 --> 00:26:00.830
It's okay to be nervous.

00:26:00.831 --> 00:26:02.206
Just be yourself.

00:26:02.207 --> 00:26:06.127
Wow. Hearing you say that
suddenly made me calm.

00:26:06.128 --> 00:26:08.922
Then hold my hand.

00:26:13.427 --> 00:26:16.471
I'm actually really nervous.

00:26:17.806 --> 00:26:20.017
Just trust me. Let's do this.

00:26:20.851 --> 00:26:22.436
Okay.

00:26:24.688 --> 00:26:26.272
You're finally here.

00:26:26.273 --> 00:26:28.442
Let's see who this guy is.

00:26:29.359 --> 00:26:31.278
Hello. I'm Cha Yougyum.

00:26:36.783 --> 00:26:38.744
It's a green light!

00:26:54.176 --> 00:26:56.844
Why did you get here late?

00:26:56.845 --> 00:26:58.472
Who did you help?

00:26:59.306 --> 00:27:00.307
An elderly woman.

00:27:01.016 --> 00:27:04.644
She was standing in the middle
of the crosswalk at a red light.

00:27:04.645 --> 00:27:06.020
It looked dangerous.

00:27:06.021 --> 00:27:08.649
Are you all right, ma'am?
Where are you headed?

00:27:09.858 --> 00:27:12.361
It seemed like she might have dementia.

00:27:13.904 --> 00:27:15.113
Oh…

00:27:24.831 --> 00:27:27.376
It's nice to meet you.

00:27:27.876 --> 00:27:30.629
Hadam doesn't know,
so pretend you never saw me.

00:27:35.175 --> 00:27:36.635
Isn't he handsome?

00:27:39.429 --> 00:27:41.890
What? Yougyum, are you crying?

00:27:42.474 --> 00:27:44.475
Huh?

00:27:44.476 --> 00:27:46.435
Oh, I…

00:27:46.436 --> 00:27:49.564
I'm just so happy
to meet your grandmother.

00:27:50.816 --> 00:27:52.149
I couldn't help it.

00:28:12.004 --> 00:28:14.006
Why aren't they picking up?

00:28:23.098 --> 00:28:26.184
My sisters aren't picking up.
We should just…

00:28:28.270 --> 00:28:29.938
Why are you sweating?

00:28:31.106 --> 00:28:33.025
- Is it hot?
- Oh.

00:28:34.609 --> 00:28:36.194
I'm not feeling so well.

00:28:38.030 --> 00:28:40.031
I'll come back when her sisters are here.

00:28:40.032 --> 00:28:41.408
- What?
- Will you?

00:28:42.409 --> 00:28:43.826
I'll see you again next time.

00:28:43.827 --> 00:28:44.911
See you at school.

00:28:47.998 --> 00:28:48.999
Yougyum!

00:28:52.961 --> 00:28:54.462
What was that, Grandma?

00:28:54.463 --> 00:28:57.631
You didn't even look at him
and didn't say a word.

00:28:57.632 --> 00:28:59.759
He left because
you made him uncomfortable.

00:28:59.760 --> 00:29:01.010
Hadam.

00:29:01.011 --> 00:29:03.095
I'm not feeling well today, either--

00:29:03.096 --> 00:29:04.847
Haran and Hayeong didn't even come.

00:29:04.848 --> 00:29:07.099
He's really important to me.
How can you do this?

00:29:07.100 --> 00:29:09.685
Did you think I was joking
about getting married?

00:29:09.686 --> 00:29:11.479
- Hadam.
- I can't believe this!

00:29:13.023 --> 00:29:14.816
- Yougyum!
- Hadam!

00:29:19.279 --> 00:29:22.032
How could he be…

00:29:31.583 --> 00:29:32.666
Hayeong!

00:29:32.667 --> 00:29:35.252
- Why are you so late?
- Well, I…

00:29:35.253 --> 00:29:36.796
- There's chalk on your face.
- Yougyum!

00:29:37.881 --> 00:29:38.882
Hadam!

00:29:39.758 --> 00:29:40.759
Did Yougyum leave?

00:29:41.968 --> 00:29:45.304
I'm sorry, things were hectic.
I didn't notice the time.

00:29:45.305 --> 00:29:46.722
I'm really sorry, too.

00:29:46.723 --> 00:29:48.682
We have a fitting tomorrow,
but the sample--

00:29:48.683 --> 00:29:50.810
Right. Sure.

00:29:50.811 --> 00:29:52.562
I'm sure you had your reasons.

00:29:53.355 --> 00:29:54.438
It's fine.

00:29:54.439 --> 00:29:56.607
You're so generous.

00:29:56.608 --> 00:29:58.067
You have a big heart…

00:29:58.068 --> 00:29:59.985
Or maybe not.

00:29:59.986 --> 00:30:02.446
You're not okay, are you?

00:30:02.447 --> 00:30:04.031
You're angry, right?

00:30:04.032 --> 00:30:05.617
Yes. Very.

00:30:06.743 --> 00:30:10.038
I'm holding back my anger,
so don't talk to me.

00:30:16.920 --> 00:30:21.215
Are you jealous because I'm doing
way better than you?

00:30:21.216 --> 00:30:22.342
You're so annoying!

00:30:29.933 --> 00:30:31.768
Oh, no…

00:30:37.232 --> 00:30:39.693
Grandma, why did Yougyum leave so quickly?

00:30:40.277 --> 00:30:42.821
Um… He must not be feeling well.

00:30:43.738 --> 00:30:46.116
I should go shower. Go upstairs.

00:30:47.951 --> 00:30:49.201
What?

00:30:49.202 --> 00:30:52.496
Doesn't Grandma seem like she's unwell?

00:30:52.497 --> 00:30:54.457
Maybe the lecture was pretty tough.

00:31:40.003 --> 00:31:42.422
Are you all right, ma'am?
Where are you headed?

00:31:44.007 --> 00:31:46.718
I'm not sure.

00:31:47.302 --> 00:31:50.263
I can't remember where I was going.

00:31:54.976 --> 00:31:57.979
It's okay. We'll cross the street together
when it's a green light.

00:32:24.214 --> 00:32:25.673
Hadam. I'm sorry.

00:32:25.674 --> 00:32:27.926
Tell Yougyum to come back next time, okay?

00:33:13.805 --> 00:33:14.806
Yes, Mr. Cha.

00:33:15.432 --> 00:33:16.598
Lunch?

00:33:16.599 --> 00:33:18.892
I'd love that. I'll head there now.

00:33:18.893 --> 00:33:21.270
- Okay.
- Ms. Song.

00:33:21.271 --> 00:33:22.314
Yes?

00:33:28.903 --> 00:33:30.195
Ms. Kim is asking for you.

00:33:30.196 --> 00:33:31.531
Me?

00:33:34.284 --> 00:33:38.287
Wait. I went there last time,
but she'd already gone home.

00:33:38.288 --> 00:33:40.998
Why do you keep playing pranks?
It doesn't suit you.

00:33:40.999 --> 00:33:43.584
I mixed up the date.
She wanted to see you today.

00:33:43.585 --> 00:33:46.045
You should go see her now.

00:33:46.046 --> 00:33:47.212
You mean it?

00:33:48.506 --> 00:33:51.468
All right, then.

00:33:54.679 --> 00:33:56.513
Yes, Mr. Cha.

00:33:56.514 --> 00:34:00.018
I don't think I can go. I'm sorry.

00:34:00.935 --> 00:34:03.562
I don't know. She keeps asking for me.

00:34:03.563 --> 00:34:04.939
MEN'S HEALTH
SEONGWON BRANCH

00:34:13.573 --> 00:34:15.700
Just a minute.

00:34:16.284 --> 00:34:17.493
Come in.

00:34:17.494 --> 00:34:19.536
Ms. Kim.

00:34:19.537 --> 00:34:21.622
I heard you asked for me.

00:34:21.623 --> 00:34:23.625
Were you dreaming? I didn't ask for you.

00:34:24.167 --> 00:34:26.543
- Get out. Don't bother me.
- Eh?

00:34:26.544 --> 00:34:30.089
What's with Mr. Yeon?
Why does he keep lying to me?

00:34:30.090 --> 00:34:31.965
I'd like you to talk to yourself outside.

00:34:31.966 --> 00:34:33.176
Okay.

00:34:33.760 --> 00:34:35.220
I'll excuse myself, then.

00:34:39.974 --> 00:34:41.309
Did I ask for her?

00:34:42.268 --> 00:34:43.269
I don't think I did.

00:35:06.000 --> 00:35:08.585
Sol, the shoulder is 17 inches, right?

00:35:08.586 --> 00:35:11.005
- Oh. One moment, please.
- Okay.

00:35:12.132 --> 00:35:14.175
What's going on? Something's off.

00:35:15.218 --> 00:35:17.636
Something's different from usual.

00:35:17.637 --> 00:35:19.639
What? What's different?

00:35:20.598 --> 00:35:21.599
What?

00:35:26.312 --> 00:35:27.438
Right. It's that.

00:35:27.439 --> 00:35:29.648
She hasn't pushed the button once today.

00:35:30.900 --> 00:35:32.360
You're right!

00:35:43.163 --> 00:35:44.788
- Are you okay?
- I'm sorry.

00:35:46.082 --> 00:35:47.374
Two, four…

00:35:47.375 --> 00:35:49.377
Look at the time.

00:35:50.044 --> 00:35:52.088
What a surprise.

00:35:53.381 --> 00:35:54.840
What? Gyeongju?

00:35:54.841 --> 00:35:56.508
The costume team, too?

00:35:56.509 --> 00:35:58.844
Yes, it was our director's idea.

00:35:58.845 --> 00:36:00.721
He said a better understanding
of the background

00:36:00.722 --> 00:36:02.890
would help with the costumes.

00:36:02.891 --> 00:36:04.058
Right.

00:36:04.768 --> 00:36:07.771
We won't be able to capture the details
with the script alone.

00:36:08.521 --> 00:36:09.522
Then shall we…

00:36:13.359 --> 00:36:14.443
Ah.

00:36:14.444 --> 00:36:16.987
My schedule's packed,

00:36:16.988 --> 00:36:20.032
so you can go as long as
it doesn't interfere with other work.

00:36:20.033 --> 00:36:22.075
I'm ready to go!

00:36:22.076 --> 00:36:25.204
I've been buried in fabric dust.
I'll finally get some fresh air!

00:36:25.205 --> 00:36:28.208
You're not going on a picnic.
Get fresh air on your day off.

00:36:29.417 --> 00:36:31.710
You know I'll work hard there.

00:36:31.711 --> 00:36:33.045
Picnic, beep.

00:36:33.046 --> 00:36:36.757
Business trip, ding ding ding.

00:36:36.758 --> 00:36:39.719
I think two nights will be enough
for your team. Is that okay?

00:36:40.220 --> 00:36:43.889
Then our costume team
will head there on Thursday.

00:36:43.890 --> 00:36:44.974
All right.

00:37:06.704 --> 00:37:07.997
Hey, Yang Changmo!

00:37:09.040 --> 00:37:10.208
Hey, Hadam.

00:37:12.001 --> 00:37:13.168
Where's Yougyum?

00:37:13.169 --> 00:37:14.670
He said he had to go somewhere.

00:37:14.671 --> 00:37:17.966
Oh… Wasn't he meeting up with you?

00:37:18.967 --> 00:37:19.968
Huh?

00:37:23.137 --> 00:37:25.013
How are we going to get through today?

00:37:25.014 --> 00:37:26.306
We do it every day.

00:37:26.307 --> 00:37:27.516
Yougyum!

00:37:27.517 --> 00:37:28.684
Hey.

00:37:28.685 --> 00:37:29.936
Go ahead.

00:37:31.145 --> 00:37:32.397
Sorry about yesterday.

00:37:33.064 --> 00:37:34.773
Let's talk after your practice.

00:37:34.774 --> 00:37:38.444
No, I'm sorry.
I didn't take care of myself properly.

00:37:39.571 --> 00:37:43.156
But sorry, Changmo asked to see me later.

00:37:43.157 --> 00:37:47.120
Maybe he needs my advice
on something.

00:37:50.832 --> 00:37:52.792
Yougyum, what are you doing?

00:37:54.085 --> 00:37:55.879
You said you're meeting Changmo.

00:37:56.754 --> 00:37:57.963
Did you meet him?

00:37:57.964 --> 00:38:00.008
What? Yes, why?

00:38:00.508 --> 00:38:02.426
- Is something up?
- Huh?

00:38:03.511 --> 00:38:05.430
No, I was just calling.

00:38:06.431 --> 00:38:07.807
Bye, then.

00:38:25.199 --> 00:38:26.200
Oh?

00:38:26.784 --> 00:38:28.243
Yougyum…

00:38:28.244 --> 00:38:29.454
Yougyum!

00:38:41.007 --> 00:38:42.300
I'll see you later.

00:38:49.807 --> 00:38:51.475
I wanted to meet you, too.

00:38:51.476 --> 00:38:53.186
Are you happy? Enjoying your date?

00:38:54.270 --> 00:38:56.730
- Hadam!
- How could you meet Han Sora--

00:38:56.731 --> 00:38:57.774
Hadam.

00:39:00.652 --> 00:39:03.363
- What are you doing here?
- I'm here too.

00:39:06.324 --> 00:39:09.284
What? You were waiting
in front of our school?

00:39:09.285 --> 00:39:10.744
You didn't even know his face.

00:39:10.745 --> 00:39:14.247
How could we not know him?
He was even on the news.

00:39:16.250 --> 00:39:17.543
They threatened you, didn't they?

00:39:18.127 --> 00:39:20.754
That's why you lied to me, right?

00:39:20.755 --> 00:39:24.383
I told him not to tell you
because we wanted to apologize.

00:39:24.384 --> 00:39:26.259
No, there's no need.

00:39:26.260 --> 00:39:28.429
I left early
because I wasn't feeling well.

00:39:29.472 --> 00:39:33.684
But who's Han Sora?
You said something about Han Sora.

00:39:33.685 --> 00:39:38.146
I don't know what you're talking about.

00:39:38.147 --> 00:39:40.441
Let's eat.

00:39:44.278 --> 00:39:46.530
Mmm. This is good.

00:39:48.449 --> 00:39:49.492
Hey, Hadam.

00:39:50.034 --> 00:39:52.120
- You said you're meeting Changmo.
- Huh?

00:39:52.704 --> 00:39:53.996
Did you meet him?

00:39:53.997 --> 00:39:56.707
What? Yes, why? Is something up?

00:39:56.708 --> 00:39:59.335
Huh? No, I was just calling.

00:40:00.003 --> 00:40:01.754
Okay.

00:40:07.093 --> 00:40:08.803
There's a visitor? Who…

00:40:14.892 --> 00:40:17.477
Is it pretty bad?

00:40:17.478 --> 00:40:19.938
My mind goes blank
from time to time.

00:40:19.939 --> 00:40:22.775
I sometimes buy the same book
two or three times.

00:40:24.318 --> 00:40:28.364
I'm usually fine,
but there are days I'm not,

00:40:30.533 --> 00:40:32.035
like the day I met you.

00:40:33.286 --> 00:40:35.663
Uh… Did you see a doctor?

00:40:37.373 --> 00:40:40.960
I got a basic checkup,
and they said there were signs.

00:40:41.544 --> 00:40:44.881
I scheduled a follow-up exam
in a few weeks.

00:40:47.008 --> 00:40:48.843
But at my age,

00:40:50.511 --> 00:40:52.346
you can sense it.

00:40:53.097 --> 00:40:55.557
It's probably right.

00:40:58.811 --> 00:41:02.314
I'm not sure what to do.

00:41:02.315 --> 00:41:04.149
You should tell your family--

00:41:04.150 --> 00:41:05.317
No.

00:41:05.318 --> 00:41:07.653
I have to focus on what I can do now.

00:41:09.072 --> 00:41:12.908
I don't know how much longer
I'll be myself.

00:41:12.909 --> 00:41:16.329
I have to take care of things
and receive treatment while I can.

00:41:19.582 --> 00:41:23.127
I'm sorry to burden you,
but please do me a favor.

00:41:24.087 --> 00:41:25.420
The fries here are good.

00:41:25.421 --> 00:41:27.255
Hadam, try this.
You like these, right?

00:41:27.256 --> 00:41:31.636
Haran has already lost
many loved ones.

00:41:32.261 --> 00:41:34.097
I don't want to be a burden to her now.

00:41:34.931 --> 00:41:37.766
Hayeong is always so loud
and quick to laugh.

00:41:37.767 --> 00:41:41.229
But if she finds out about my condition,
she won't be able to smile again.

00:41:42.939 --> 00:41:44.315
Hadam's in her senior year.

00:41:44.816 --> 00:41:48.277
She needs to focus on her studies.
I won't be the reason she falls apart.

00:41:49.070 --> 00:41:50.488
So please...

00:41:51.948 --> 00:41:52.949
For now,

00:41:53.574 --> 00:41:55.660
keep this a secret.

00:42:03.876 --> 00:42:05.878
I don't have much time.

00:42:11.968 --> 00:42:14.762
How badly did they scrape it?

00:42:15.596 --> 00:42:18.598
Are you the one who called me
about the accident?

00:42:23.688 --> 00:42:26.606
I did call you, but there was no accident.

00:42:26.607 --> 00:42:29.277
What… Then why would you say
there was an accident?

00:42:30.361 --> 00:42:31.862
Hang on.

00:42:31.863 --> 00:42:33.071
It's you, isn't it?

00:42:33.072 --> 00:42:35.074
- I have it all planned out.
- Mr. Cha Min?

00:42:37.577 --> 00:42:39.703
I'll treat you to something nice.

00:42:55.678 --> 00:42:57.680
What was that? What's with him?

00:42:58.472 --> 00:43:01.141
The guy in the hotel parking lot
who reversed into me.

00:43:01.142 --> 00:43:02.517
Who are you--

00:43:02.518 --> 00:43:04.020
That's not your business.

00:43:05.104 --> 00:43:09.232
Why don't you sort out
all the women you've been juggling?

00:43:09.233 --> 00:43:12.402
What are you saying?
Who are you to order me around?

00:43:12.403 --> 00:43:15.363
It would be best
to say you got transferred abroad

00:43:15.364 --> 00:43:16.823
so no one feels hurt.

00:43:16.824 --> 00:43:19.744
If you don't stop acting like a scumbag,

00:43:21.454 --> 00:43:23.581
we'll be meeting again.

00:43:26.542 --> 00:43:27.835
Hey!

00:43:30.171 --> 00:43:32.547
That's what you call being a scumbag.

00:43:32.548 --> 00:43:34.841
Do you want the other one broken, too?

00:43:34.842 --> 00:43:37.553
Whether you break it or not,
just sort out your women problem.

00:43:38.137 --> 00:43:40.972
I suggest sending out DMs right now.

00:43:40.973 --> 00:43:44.851
Mmm… No, thanks.

00:43:44.852 --> 00:43:47.062
I'm not going to.

00:43:47.063 --> 00:43:49.689
It's all because I'm popular.

00:43:49.690 --> 00:43:51.566
What are you going to do?

00:43:51.567 --> 00:43:52.651
Oh…

00:43:52.652 --> 00:43:54.320
Wait. Hey. Hey!

00:43:55.071 --> 00:43:56.656
My phone.

00:43:58.824 --> 00:43:59.825
Hey!

00:44:01.285 --> 00:44:02.786
If you don't sort them out,

00:44:02.787 --> 00:44:04.622
the next thing you'll lose…

00:44:06.582 --> 00:44:08.292
won't be your phone.

00:44:15.341 --> 00:44:16.424
Wait.

00:44:16.425 --> 00:44:17.802
- Hang on.
- Hello.

00:44:18.594 --> 00:44:20.888
I want to schedule a car repair.

00:44:21.472 --> 00:44:22.722
My phone's in there.

00:44:22.723 --> 00:44:24.766
What are you doing?

00:44:24.767 --> 00:44:27.019
I'm heading out!

00:44:30.022 --> 00:44:32.023
- Whoa. Oh…
- I'll drive.

00:44:32.024 --> 00:44:33.858
What are you doing here?

00:44:33.859 --> 00:44:35.402
We're going to Gyeongju.

00:44:35.403 --> 00:44:37.529
I'm going to Gyeongju,
but the costume team--

00:44:37.530 --> 00:44:38.822
I'm going today, too.

00:44:38.823 --> 00:44:40.740
Can you load my luggage?

00:44:40.741 --> 00:44:41.825
Oh…

00:44:43.703 --> 00:44:44.704
Sure…

00:44:47.873 --> 00:44:48.874
Mmm…

00:44:50.126 --> 00:44:52.460
Wow. I feel pretty happy.

00:44:52.461 --> 00:44:54.672
You're worried about me.

00:44:55.381 --> 00:44:56.923
Worried?

00:44:56.924 --> 00:44:57.925
Me?

00:44:58.634 --> 00:45:02.929
You were worried about
me driving after what happened last time.

00:45:02.930 --> 00:45:04.307
When did I…

00:45:07.143 --> 00:45:08.977
You're right.

00:45:08.978 --> 00:45:11.605
It must be your first time
driving on a highway in Korea.

00:45:13.107 --> 00:45:14.191
Thanks.

00:45:19.363 --> 00:45:22.032
But do you usually do
field research for animations?

00:45:22.033 --> 00:45:23.075
Of course.

00:45:23.701 --> 00:45:26.077
You know Arendelle, right?

00:45:26.078 --> 00:45:29.873
That was based on
a lakeside town called Hallstatt.

00:45:29.874 --> 00:45:36.839
And the ice castle was inspired
by a hotel built of ice in Quebec.

00:45:37.423 --> 00:45:39.382
And Won is Korean,

00:45:39.383 --> 00:45:41.635
so we're looking
for her background in Korea.

00:45:42.178 --> 00:45:45.013
We have to decide
where she grew up and how

00:45:45.014 --> 00:45:47.474
so we can blend that into the story.

00:45:47.475 --> 00:45:51.603
You had the vibe of a local bum,
but you seem like a pro now.

00:45:51.604 --> 00:45:52.812
A local bum?

00:45:52.813 --> 00:45:54.314
Geez.

00:45:54.315 --> 00:45:57.650
I didn't want to say this myself,
but I'll just say it.

00:45:57.651 --> 00:45:59.736
I'm pretty competent.

00:45:59.737 --> 00:46:01.571
I get lots of job offers, too.

00:46:01.572 --> 00:46:02.989
I meant it's nice

00:46:02.990 --> 00:46:05.576
seeing you look so excited
talking about work.

00:46:09.080 --> 00:46:10.163
Hang on.

00:46:11.832 --> 00:46:12.833
Hey, Ben.

00:46:14.001 --> 00:46:15.251
Well, we're…

00:46:15.252 --> 00:46:16.754
We're almost halfway there.

00:46:17.588 --> 00:46:18.881
We're almost halfway there.

00:46:19.465 --> 00:46:21.967
Oh. I'm going with Ms. Song.

00:46:23.094 --> 00:46:24.427
It just happened.

00:46:24.428 --> 00:46:25.553
See you later.

00:46:29.809 --> 00:46:31.936
I can smell rain.

00:46:45.116 --> 00:46:46.659
Is it a shower?

00:46:47.952 --> 00:46:48.953
Mmm.

00:46:49.453 --> 00:46:52.956
But I heard it's the smell
of organic matter diffusing,

00:46:52.957 --> 00:46:54.499
not the rain.

00:46:54.500 --> 00:46:56.626
- What was it again?
- Petrichor.

00:46:56.627 --> 00:46:57.711
Right, petrichor.

00:46:58.796 --> 00:47:00.463
You're really good at this stuff.

00:47:00.464 --> 00:47:03.384
You said something about hypochlorite
at the police station, too.

00:47:04.218 --> 00:47:06.470
It seems like you majored
in engineering, not art.

00:47:12.852 --> 00:47:15.562
Oh? It stopped. What's going on?

00:47:15.563 --> 00:47:16.729
Huh?

00:47:16.730 --> 00:47:17.857
Is it not working?

00:47:18.357 --> 00:47:20.233
No. Didn't they check this car?

00:47:20.234 --> 00:47:21.861
I got it checked.

00:47:23.237 --> 00:47:25.780
It's not raining much yet, though.

00:47:28.200 --> 00:47:29.367
What…

00:47:29.368 --> 00:47:31.494
Wait. It's raining too much.

00:47:31.495 --> 00:47:33.037
Just pull over to the side.

00:47:33.038 --> 00:47:34.330
Pull over?

00:47:36.834 --> 00:47:38.209
UNDER CONSTRUCTION
NO SHOULDER AHEAD

00:47:38.210 --> 00:47:40.628
Huh? "No shoulder ahead"?

00:47:40.629 --> 00:47:42.046
Then what do we do?

00:47:42.047 --> 00:47:44.007
It's not like we can make a road.

00:47:44.008 --> 00:47:46.092
- First…
- Check if there are any cars.

00:47:46.093 --> 00:47:47.760
Hang on. I'll take care of it.

00:47:48.929 --> 00:47:50.972
Oh no. I can't see anything. What do I do?

00:47:50.973 --> 00:47:52.892
Wait.

00:47:53.893 --> 00:47:55.603
- Hang on.
- I can't see anything.

00:47:58.731 --> 00:48:00.773
- What are you doing?
- This won't work.

00:48:00.774 --> 00:48:02.567
Check if there are any cars coming!

00:48:02.568 --> 00:48:03.693
I can't see anything.

00:48:03.694 --> 00:48:05.111
SOMUNGYEONG REST STOP

00:48:05.112 --> 00:48:06.988
- It's a rest stop!
- A rest stop?

00:48:06.989 --> 00:48:08.573
I can't see the road, though.

00:48:08.574 --> 00:48:12.952
I'll keep my eye on the road,
so keep driving.

00:48:12.953 --> 00:48:14.037
But I can't see.

00:48:14.038 --> 00:48:15.914
I'll count to three,

00:48:15.915 --> 00:48:18.583
- so turn right when I get to three.
- Okay.

00:48:18.584 --> 00:48:19.667
All right…

00:48:19.668 --> 00:48:21.712
One, two,

00:48:22.630 --> 00:48:23.713
three.

00:48:28.469 --> 00:48:31.472
SOMUNGYEONG REST STOP

00:48:51.033 --> 00:48:52.200
Ah…

00:48:52.201 --> 00:48:53.910
Take a breather.

00:48:53.911 --> 00:48:55.871
I'll call the rental shop.

00:48:56.497 --> 00:48:57.706
Oh…

00:49:03.796 --> 00:49:05.923
What? Four to five hours?

00:49:07.299 --> 00:49:08.675
The motor's completely out.

00:49:08.676 --> 00:49:10.009
We can't fix it here.

00:49:10.010 --> 00:49:12.178
I'll take it to a repair shop nearby.

00:49:12.179 --> 00:49:15.599
If you want a replacement,
we'll send you another car tomorrow.

00:49:16.183 --> 00:49:17.226
I'm sorry.

00:49:25.442 --> 00:49:27.861
Yes, we probably won't get there
until tonight.

00:49:29.196 --> 00:49:31.865
Okay, Ben. I'll call you again
when we're heading out.

00:49:32.491 --> 00:49:33.576
Okay.

00:49:41.000 --> 00:49:42.458
Here, wipe yourself up.

00:49:42.459 --> 00:49:43.961
It's fine.

00:49:44.878 --> 00:49:47.298
You really don't listen.

00:50:07.693 --> 00:50:09.820
How are we going to wait here for hours?

00:50:11.822 --> 00:50:16.492
There's someone in Mungyeong Saejae
I can ask for help.

00:50:30.007 --> 00:50:31.008
Seonu Chan!

00:50:32.718 --> 00:50:35.012
Wow, that was fast.

00:50:35.804 --> 00:50:38.348
You little brat.

00:50:38.349 --> 00:50:40.266
You should've told me you came to Korea.

00:50:40.267 --> 00:50:42.685
You only called me now?

00:50:42.686 --> 00:50:43.770
Sorry.

00:50:43.771 --> 00:50:45.730
Oh, my.

00:50:45.731 --> 00:50:48.024
- Did you take ginseng?
- Yes.

00:50:48.025 --> 00:50:50.360
- You look so healthy.
- Right?

00:50:52.112 --> 00:50:53.322
Oh, dear.

00:50:54.073 --> 00:50:55.365
Goodness.

00:50:55.366 --> 00:50:59.160
This is Designer Song Haran,
who's working with me.

00:50:59.161 --> 00:51:00.329
Say hi.

00:51:00.913 --> 00:51:02.497
She's my grandmother.

00:51:02.498 --> 00:51:03.581
Grandmother?

00:51:03.582 --> 00:51:04.666
Hello.

00:51:06.418 --> 00:51:09.421
I haven't really made
a great first impression.

00:51:10.089 --> 00:51:11.757
- Nice to meet you.
- Hello.

00:51:15.594 --> 00:51:16.970
Let's go.

00:51:31.068 --> 00:51:34.154
- Isn't that a waste?
- You think so?

00:51:34.780 --> 00:51:38.658
But we have to empty it out a few times
to get rid of the impurities.

00:51:38.659 --> 00:51:41.286
It makes the flavor
much smoother this way.

00:51:42.204 --> 00:51:44.038
It's the same with people.

00:51:44.039 --> 00:51:47.709
We have to empty ourselves out
from time to time

00:51:47.710 --> 00:51:51.213
to clear our heads and soften our hearts.

00:51:52.756 --> 00:51:54.590
The color's nice.

00:51:54.591 --> 00:51:56.844
- Try it.
- Thank you.

00:51:58.512 --> 00:52:01.223
It's hot. Cool it down a bit.

00:52:02.307 --> 00:52:03.516
It's okay, it's not hot.

00:52:05.561 --> 00:52:06.978
You're right. It's not.

00:52:06.979 --> 00:52:09.439
How about some coffee?
I brought Mr. Park's coffee beans.

00:52:09.440 --> 00:52:11.274
I'll go and…

00:52:11.275 --> 00:52:13.819
I'd prefer tea right now.

00:52:18.615 --> 00:52:21.367
- It's delicious.
- Right?

00:52:21.368 --> 00:52:22.369
Wow.

00:52:23.036 --> 00:52:26.372
The teapot and this cup…

00:52:26.373 --> 00:52:28.625
Everything here is so beautiful.

00:52:29.501 --> 00:52:32.713
They were all made by my grandma.

00:52:33.964 --> 00:52:34.965
She's a potter.

00:52:36.049 --> 00:52:38.468
The building outside is my studio.

00:52:38.469 --> 00:52:40.928
Would you care to take a look
once you're done?

00:52:46.852 --> 00:52:48.144
Oh…

00:52:48.145 --> 00:52:50.897
Yes… I'd love to take a look.

00:52:50.898 --> 00:52:52.316
Hey, Chaewon.

00:52:54.943 --> 00:52:56.403
What do you mean, you're sorry?

00:53:04.203 --> 00:53:05.286
What are you doing?

00:53:05.287 --> 00:53:09.332
Savoring the only meal I'm having
to get my jawline back.

00:53:12.961 --> 00:53:15.297
- Oh, my gosh.
- Samples are here!

00:53:18.342 --> 00:53:19.343
My sweet potato.

00:53:20.010 --> 00:53:23.262
I feel like
I swallowed a sock.

00:53:23.263 --> 00:53:25.973
What is it? Did something piss you off?

00:53:25.974 --> 00:53:28.476
You know the guy I was seeing?

00:53:28.477 --> 00:53:30.353
He cheated.

00:53:30.354 --> 00:53:32.814
The guy who sent the flowers?

00:53:32.815 --> 00:53:34.358
That son of a…

00:53:34.942 --> 00:53:37.361
I shouldn't swear. With who?

00:53:38.487 --> 00:53:40.989
With me. I'm the other woman.

00:53:41.698 --> 00:53:46.244
He made a ton of social media accounts
and used them to hit on girls.

00:53:46.245 --> 00:53:49.622
And I just heard
he's giving out wedding invitations.

00:53:49.623 --> 00:53:52.876
That jerk!
Should I just beat him up?

00:53:53.669 --> 00:53:56.337
Never mind. Just forget it
and pretend nothing happened.

00:53:56.338 --> 00:53:58.674
Why would I just forget about it?

00:54:00.801 --> 00:54:02.928
I'm going to crush him.

00:54:07.474 --> 00:54:14.021
♪ Happy wedding to you ♪

00:54:14.022 --> 00:54:17.316
♪ Happy wedding, dear Cha Min ♪

00:54:17.317 --> 00:54:19.152
♪ Happy wedding… ♪

00:54:19.987 --> 00:54:21.654
Ms. Song.

00:54:21.655 --> 00:54:24.032
Were you pleased
with your wedding invitations?

00:54:30.789 --> 00:54:32.124
If you found out, just go.

00:54:33.584 --> 00:54:35.126
I guess it was you.

00:54:35.127 --> 00:54:37.503
I was wondering why
some guy was picking a fight.

00:54:37.504 --> 00:54:39.672
Was he your boyfriend?

00:54:39.673 --> 00:54:41.007
What are you saying?

00:54:41.008 --> 00:54:42.967
How would you meet
a boyfriend I don't have?

00:54:42.968 --> 00:54:44.218
Boom!

00:54:44.219 --> 00:54:47.430
He threatened me with his car
and threw my phone into a mop bucket.

00:54:47.431 --> 00:54:49.933
Geez. I should've broken
both his rear-view mirrors.

00:54:50.809 --> 00:54:53.769
Tell that jerk to watch his back at night.

00:54:53.770 --> 00:54:54.937
Quit the nonsense.

00:54:54.938 --> 00:54:57.315
You should watch your back, day and night.

00:54:57.316 --> 00:54:59.567
You should sleep with one eye open.

00:54:59.568 --> 00:55:01.611
You never know when I'll crush you.

00:55:01.612 --> 00:55:03.530
Forget it. Just go.

00:55:05.073 --> 00:55:06.199
I'm not done yet.

00:55:14.249 --> 00:55:15.500
My nose…

00:55:16.168 --> 00:55:18.378
I paid a fortune for this.

00:55:19.254 --> 00:55:20.672
- Hey!
- What?

00:55:21.840 --> 00:55:23.215
You.

00:55:23.216 --> 00:55:25.177
You'd better stay out of my sight.

00:55:26.053 --> 00:55:27.596
Or I'll kick you somewhere else.

00:55:53.997 --> 00:55:55.373
Did you go somewhere?

00:55:55.374 --> 00:55:56.832
I had a meeting.

00:55:56.833 --> 00:55:58.292
Ah…

00:55:58.293 --> 00:56:01.755
But is there something wrong?
You seem pretty down.

00:56:02.714 --> 00:56:04.341
What? No.

00:56:05.133 --> 00:56:06.385
I'm fine.

00:56:07.177 --> 00:56:09.845
But why were you riding a cab?

00:56:09.846 --> 00:56:11.806
You always drive.

00:56:11.807 --> 00:56:14.767
Uh… I had to get it repaired.

00:56:14.768 --> 00:56:16.311
Ah. I see.

00:56:17.437 --> 00:56:20.273
Head inside.
I'm going to go get some coffee.

00:56:25.404 --> 00:56:28.031
I was wondering why
some guy was picking a fight.

00:56:29.157 --> 00:56:31.117
I should've broken
both his rear-view mirrors.

00:56:31.118 --> 00:56:33.619
"Cha Min." Even his name is nice.

00:56:33.620 --> 00:56:36.706
- What do you think, Mr. Yeon?
- I'm not so sure.

00:56:36.707 --> 00:56:39.709
- But, Mr. Cha…
- Ms. Kim wants you in her office.

00:56:41.086 --> 00:56:42.504
Are you…

00:56:43.630 --> 00:56:46.799
getting it repaired
because of your rear-view mirror?

00:56:46.800 --> 00:56:48.175
Yes.

00:56:48.176 --> 00:56:49.260
But why…

00:56:49.261 --> 00:56:51.680
Are you the one who met Cha Min?

00:56:53.515 --> 00:56:54.598
Uh…

00:56:54.599 --> 00:56:58.310
I have no idea what you're talking about.

00:56:58.311 --> 00:57:01.021
Oh. You really have no idea?

00:57:01.022 --> 00:57:04.609
Okay, then I'll just go meet him.

00:57:05.569 --> 00:57:08.321
Cha Min's number was…

00:57:10.782 --> 00:57:13.702
Are you going to say
"Ms. Kim is asking for you" again?

00:57:22.461 --> 00:57:25.421
Yes, Ms. Kim. I'll be there straightaway.

00:57:25.422 --> 00:57:27.132
You didn't even get a call.

00:57:28.467 --> 00:57:29.967
And she already got off work.

00:57:29.968 --> 00:57:31.552
Yes, I'm on my way.

00:57:31.553 --> 00:57:33.680
You're holding your phone upside down!

00:57:34.765 --> 00:57:36.475
Gosh, what's with him?

00:57:42.314 --> 00:57:44.775
Wait. No way…

00:57:48.236 --> 00:57:50.781
It can't be, right?

00:57:56.912 --> 00:57:58.038
Wow.

00:57:59.039 --> 00:58:00.040
Wow.

00:58:01.291 --> 00:58:04.752
Wow, they're so beautiful.

00:58:04.753 --> 00:58:07.380
Take some you like.

00:58:08.173 --> 00:58:10.592
They're not even yours. Huh?

00:58:11.259 --> 00:58:13.844
What's this drawing?

00:58:13.845 --> 00:58:15.180
- Did you draw this, too?
- Oh…

00:58:15.931 --> 00:58:18.016
Would you like to try
making something here?

00:58:19.851 --> 00:58:21.561
The aprons…

00:58:38.286 --> 00:58:39.287
I'm done.

00:58:39.788 --> 00:58:41.998
Already?

00:58:42.791 --> 00:58:44.793
Oh, no! Wait.

00:58:48.839 --> 00:58:50.298
That was close.

00:58:55.095 --> 00:58:56.512
Let me take this call.

00:58:56.513 --> 00:58:57.556
Sure.

00:58:58.974 --> 00:59:00.058
Hello?

00:59:06.106 --> 00:59:08.649
It's so pretty.

00:59:08.650 --> 00:59:11.443
How about becoming my pupil?

00:59:11.444 --> 00:59:14.154
I mean it.

00:59:14.155 --> 00:59:16.365
Leave me your address and phone number.

00:59:16.366 --> 00:59:17.992
I'll fire it nicely and send it to you.

00:59:17.993 --> 00:59:19.661
Thank you.

00:59:20.537 --> 00:59:22.873
I guess Mr. Seonu
inherited his gift from you.

00:59:23.874 --> 00:59:27.627
That drawing was his mother's.

00:59:29.087 --> 00:59:30.754
My daughter was an artist too.

00:59:30.755 --> 00:59:33.884
Ah. So he took after his mother.

00:59:34.384 --> 00:59:38.722
He and my daughter would draw
on any piece of paper they could find.

00:59:42.475 --> 00:59:43.935
Wait here.

00:59:47.856 --> 00:59:51.776
They're pictures he drew
whenever he came here as a child.

00:59:54.362 --> 00:59:56.740
He was so excited
when he talked about work.

00:59:57.324 --> 00:59:59.159
I guess he really loved drawing.

01:00:00.493 --> 01:00:03.829
If his dad hadn't hated it so much,

01:00:03.830 --> 01:00:06.124
he would have enjoyed it much more.

01:00:08.835 --> 01:00:09.836
Ah.

01:00:10.754 --> 01:00:14.090
His father hated him doing art.

01:00:15.467 --> 01:00:17.761
But you said his mother was an artist…

01:00:19.262 --> 01:00:23.642
Her dream was to go abroad
and study more art.

01:00:24.309 --> 01:00:28.395
And Chan's father wanted her
to wait until Chan was older.

01:00:28.396 --> 01:00:29.939
Look!

01:00:29.940 --> 01:00:31.899
Why do we have
to keep arguing over this?

01:00:31.900 --> 01:00:33.192
Don't you understand?

01:00:33.193 --> 01:00:36.278
Why now? Why do you have
to go abroad to study?

01:00:36.279 --> 01:00:39.990
You know it's been my dream
since before we got married.

01:00:39.991 --> 01:00:43.327
I want to study properly
before it's too late.

01:00:43.328 --> 01:00:44.495
Fine. Do it.

01:00:44.496 --> 01:00:48.582
You can study here and think about it
again when Chan is older.

01:00:48.583 --> 01:00:50.460
You're hardly home anyway!

01:00:51.711 --> 01:00:54.421
You can stay in your lab
all you want. I'll take Chan--

01:00:54.422 --> 01:00:55.548
If you must go,

01:00:56.841 --> 01:00:58.550
then leave Chan and go by yourself.

01:00:58.551 --> 01:01:02.347
She still wanted to go so badly.

01:01:02.973 --> 01:01:06.684
So I pushed her to follow her dream

01:01:06.685 --> 01:01:09.437
and do what she wanted.

01:01:10.313 --> 01:01:14.274
She thought she had to settle down quickly
to be with Chan again,

01:01:14.275 --> 01:01:17.153
so she pushed herself too hard.

01:01:17.904 --> 01:01:19.655
And she got sick.

01:01:19.656 --> 01:01:22.784
Soon after she left the country,

01:01:23.660 --> 01:01:25.120
she...

01:01:26.705 --> 01:01:27.706
Chan!

01:01:29.374 --> 01:01:30.749
Oh, no!

01:01:30.750 --> 01:01:32.335
I can't believe what happened…

01:01:32.877 --> 01:01:36.006
He said he'd never let Chan paint again.

01:01:36.589 --> 01:01:39.551
So he sent him to America.

01:01:40.135 --> 01:01:42.762
Chan didn't get to do anything he loved,

01:01:43.388 --> 01:01:46.473
and he suffered there.

01:01:51.730 --> 01:01:53.188
KSU
KOREA SCIENCE UNIVERSITY

01:01:53.189 --> 01:01:59.029
It would've been painful
for Chan's father just to see him paint.

01:02:00.321 --> 01:02:02.614
He thinks Chan's mom left to paint...

01:02:02.615 --> 01:02:04.533
KOREAN ANIMATORS IN THE GLOBAL SPOTLIGHT

01:02:04.534 --> 01:02:07.328
...and died because of it.

01:02:09.122 --> 01:02:10.540
Okay, bye.

01:02:11.374 --> 01:02:14.626
Back then,
my daughter was all I could think about.

01:02:14.627 --> 01:02:18.465
But whenever I see Chan,
it breaks my heart.

01:02:18.923 --> 01:02:21.842
If he had his mother,

01:02:21.843 --> 01:02:25.972
at least he wouldn't have been hurt
both emotionally and physically.

01:02:26.931 --> 01:02:28.141
I've also been trapped

01:02:29.059 --> 01:02:31.311
in a long winter all by myself.

01:02:40.195 --> 01:02:41.196
Oh?

01:02:41.863 --> 01:02:43.030
Where's Ms. Song?

01:02:43.031 --> 01:02:44.532
- She's washing her hands.
- Oh.

01:02:47.494 --> 01:02:49.162
Is it just one-sided at the moment?

01:02:49.913 --> 01:02:50.914
What do you mean?

01:02:53.583 --> 01:02:55.751
Gosh, Grandma. It's not like that.

01:02:55.752 --> 01:02:57.253
Don't be silly.

01:02:57.837 --> 01:02:58.880
I can see it clearly.

01:02:59.714 --> 01:03:01.965
You have a crush on Ms. Song, don't you?

01:03:01.966 --> 01:03:03.885
It's not like that.

01:03:05.178 --> 01:03:07.429
She's someone I shouldn't like.

01:03:07.430 --> 01:03:09.557
What do you mean, someone you shouldn't…

01:03:10.141 --> 01:03:13.143
Hey.
Is she married, by any chance?

01:03:13.144 --> 01:03:14.603
No, she's not married.

01:03:14.604 --> 01:03:17.148
Then why would you say
you shouldn't like her?

01:03:17.774 --> 01:03:19.942
Ma'am, can I get a towel?

01:03:19.943 --> 01:03:21.778
Sure. Hang on.

01:03:30.912 --> 01:03:33.748
How could I like her?

01:03:35.250 --> 01:03:36.417
That would be selfish.

01:03:37.752 --> 01:03:41.338
Visit me again next time.
You can come without that chatterbox.

01:03:41.339 --> 01:03:43.841
Sure. I'll come without that chatterbox
next time.

01:03:45.301 --> 01:03:47.594
Don't build your friendship
by badmouthing me.

01:03:49.472 --> 01:03:52.182
It was so nice to meet you.

01:03:52.183 --> 01:03:54.393
- Take care.
- Stay healthy, ma'am.

01:03:56.437 --> 01:03:58.648
Um… Wait.

01:04:00.859 --> 01:04:02.442
What's that?

01:04:02.443 --> 01:04:04.779
Pardon me.

01:04:05.405 --> 01:04:06.655
This is really moisturizing.

01:04:08.032 --> 01:04:09.616
My hands are pretty rough, right?

01:04:09.617 --> 01:04:11.535
I'm always touching clay.

01:04:11.536 --> 01:04:13.036
Here, use this.

01:04:13.037 --> 01:04:17.166
I'll get pretty hands thanks to you.

01:04:17.167 --> 01:04:18.501
Let's see…

01:04:19.085 --> 01:04:22.629
You know, no matter how warm you dress,

01:04:22.630 --> 01:04:25.174
you'll catch a cold
if you don't cover your neck.

01:04:25.175 --> 01:04:27.217
- I'm okay.
- No, come here.

01:04:27.218 --> 01:04:29.012
Here.

01:04:29.929 --> 01:04:32.222
Just take it.
You ruined your scarf because of me.

01:04:32.223 --> 01:04:33.348
Hmm? Did she?

01:04:33.349 --> 01:04:35.559
Wow, look.

01:04:35.560 --> 01:04:38.228
It looks incredible on a beautiful model.

01:04:38.229 --> 01:04:39.563
Nice. This is great.

01:04:39.564 --> 01:04:41.940
Thank you. I'll use it well.

01:04:41.941 --> 01:04:43.443
Grandma.

01:04:45.737 --> 01:04:48.197
I'll come back before I go back to the US.

01:04:49.282 --> 01:04:51.326
You'd better keep your word.

01:04:52.994 --> 01:04:54.621
Chan, please. Hmm?

01:04:55.455 --> 01:04:57.123
Don't skip your meals. Okay?

01:04:57.624 --> 01:04:59.167
Of course. I eat well.

01:04:59.751 --> 01:05:01.668
You too, Grandma.

01:05:01.669 --> 01:05:03.546
- Don't worry.
- Okay.

01:05:05.256 --> 01:05:06.840
Bye!

01:05:06.841 --> 01:05:08.092
Drive safely!

01:05:14.390 --> 01:05:17.685
Wait. Let's check the windshield wipers
one more time.

01:05:18.269 --> 01:05:19.520
- Again?
- Yes.

01:05:24.025 --> 01:05:25.484
- Are we good?
- Wait.

01:05:29.489 --> 01:05:32.909
Okay. Done. Let's go.

01:05:36.746 --> 01:05:38.706
What? Is there something wrong again?

01:05:39.374 --> 01:05:41.167
Yes, there is.

01:05:41.793 --> 01:05:42.794
Something strange.

01:05:44.128 --> 01:05:45.588
What's strange?

01:05:48.549 --> 01:05:51.970
Why am I someone you shouldn't like?

01:05:53.721 --> 01:05:54.847
What?

01:05:56.391 --> 01:05:58.268
Why shouldn't you like me?

01:06:01.396 --> 01:06:03.898
You have a crush on Ms. Song, don't you?

01:06:04.524 --> 01:06:05.775
It's not like that.

01:06:06.359 --> 01:06:07.944
She's someone I shouldn't like.

01:06:09.195 --> 01:06:11.114
What do you mean, someone you shouldn't…

01:06:12.240 --> 01:06:15.158
Hey.
Is she married, by any chance?

01:06:15.159 --> 01:06:16.743
No, she's not married.

01:06:16.744 --> 01:06:19.371
Then why would you say
you shouldn't like her?

01:06:19.372 --> 01:06:21.623
Ma'am, can I get a towel?

01:06:21.624 --> 01:06:24.042
Sure. Hang on.

01:06:24.043 --> 01:06:26.337
I'm sorry, but I overheard.

01:06:26.963 --> 01:06:29.215
I really couldn't understand, though.

01:06:29.924 --> 01:06:32.259
You weren't saying
that you didn't like me.

01:06:32.260 --> 01:06:36.264
You said you shouldn't like me.
That sounds weird.

01:06:42.186 --> 01:06:43.729
It's not like I'm married.

01:06:43.730 --> 01:06:46.899
There's nothing between us
that would make it wrong.

01:06:47.734 --> 01:06:49.319
What did you mean by that?

01:06:53.906 --> 01:06:58.076
Oh… I'm not trying to argue or anything.
I'm just genuinely curious.

01:06:58.077 --> 01:06:59.828
Then is it okay if I like you?

01:07:41.871 --> 01:07:43.790
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:08:08.314 --> 01:08:11.775
The person
who gave me the pen died.

01:08:11.776 --> 01:08:15.612
What else was there
apart from the explosion?

01:08:15.613 --> 01:08:17.489
Honestly, I am curious.

01:08:17.490 --> 01:08:20.993
You're not telling me everything.

01:08:21.994 --> 01:08:26.499
The past might not be
as nice as you remember.

01:08:27.125 --> 01:08:29.918
I'll explain everything
if you guess it right.

01:08:29.919 --> 01:08:33.631
I feel like telling you everything today.

01:08:34.507 --> 01:08:35.550
Odd.

01:08:36.467 --> 01:08:37.593
Odd.

01:08:49.647 --> 01:08:50.730
IN YOUR RADIANT SEASON

01:08:50.731 --> 01:08:51.732
Translated by Juyoung Park